    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "THE TRIBUNE: WEDNESDAY, JUNE 5, 1935\nSOCIETY PAGE\nOffice Tel. 2-11-34\nCORAZON E. GRAU, Editor\nGovernor and Mrs. Hayden at Home at Malacañanz\nThe recewing line at Malacañang Palace yesterday afternoon when Acting Governor\nmembers of the Forbes Mission.\nGeneral and Mrs.\nHayden and Acting Governor General Hayden.\nFrom the left are H. M. Bixby, Dr. L. C. Jones, Mrs. T. W. Wickham,\nHayden were at home for the\nT. W. Wickham, Mrs. J. Ralston\nA. gathering\nyesterday. On the extreme left is Mrs. Eulogio Rodriguez, wife of Secretary\nof men and women from the cosmopolitan community of Manita called\nRodrigues of agriculture and commerce, who presided over\nover the tea table, together with Mrs. H. B. Pond, extreme right."
    ],
